&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Global Supply Chain Manager – EMEA is responsible for developing and executing end-to-end supply chain strategies that optimise cost, service, risk, and sustainability across CoreWeave’s international operations. This is a varied, hands-on role spanning procurement support, logistics coordination, inventory management, and supplier performance across a rapidly growing international portfolio. The ideal candidate is a strategic thinker with deep operational expertise, strong cross-functional leadership, and the ability to navigate country-specific regulations, customs requirements, and trade compliance across diverse international markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategy &amp;amp; Execution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the design and execution of supply chain strategies to meet business objectives and customer requirements across EMEA.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support global procurement and sourcing operations, ensuring cost-effective and reliable material supply across regions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and manage KPIs to measure supply chain performance, risk, and cost efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop risk mitigation strategies, including supply chain diversification, dual sourcing, and business continuity planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logistics &amp;amp; International Movements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the logistics team to ensure smooth international movements, bringing knowledge of country-specific customs rules, VAT regimes, import requirements, and incoterms to each shipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure correct incoterms are applied to protect CoreWeave from unnecessary VAT and import duty exposure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor inbound and outbound shipment movements, partnering closely with Data Centre teams to align on delivery scheduling and factor site-specific challenges into supply chain planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inventory &amp;amp; Supplier Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee inventory management across EMEA, including safety stock, surplus materials, and site transfers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and support supplier and logistics provider relationships, driving performance, accountability, and continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track material availability against build timelines, proactively identifying and escalating risks to senior leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
